This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the detection of pulmonary nodules in CT scans using convolutional neural networks. The use of MIP images also suggests that it could be related to medical imaging (cs.MS) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of CNNs for automatic detection also suggests that it could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
